---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "../components/shared/Container.astro";

const LAST_UPDATED = "October 17, 2025";
---

<Layout title="Terms & Conditions">
  <main class="py-10 sm:py-16">
    <Container className="max-w-4xl space-y-10">
      <header class="space-y-3">
        <h1
          class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900"
        >
          Terms & Conditions
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: {LAST_UPDATED}</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          These Terms & Conditions (“<strong>Terms</strong>”) govern your access
          to and use of the Protize website, products, and services
          (collectively, the “<strong>Services</strong>”) provided by
          <strong>Protize</strong> (“<strong>we</strong>”, “<strong>us</strong
          >”, “<strong>our</strong>”). By accessing or using the Services, you
          agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the
          Services.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Acceptance & Changes -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          1) Acceptance of Terms & Changes
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Your use of the Services constitutes acceptance of these Terms. We may
          revise these Terms at any time by posting an updated version with the
          “Last updated” date shown above. Material changes may be communicated
          via email or site notice. Your continued use after changes indicates
          acceptance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Eligibility -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">2) Eligibility</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          You must be at least the age of majority in your jurisdiction, or have
          valid consent from a parent/guardian, to use the Services. If you are
          accessing on behalf of an organization, you represent that you have
          authority to bind that organization to these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Accounts -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">3) Accounts & Security</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
          <li>
            You agree to provide accurate, complete information and keep it
            updated.
          </li>
          <li>
            You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your
            credentials and for all activities under your account.
          </li>
          <li>
            Notify us promptly of any unauthorized use or security incident.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Acceptable Use -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">4) Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">You agree not to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
          <li>Violate any applicable law or regulation.</li>
          <li>
            Infringe, misappropriate, or violate intellectual property or
            privacy rights.
          </li>
          <li>Upload or transmit malicious code, spam, or illegal content.</li>
          <li>
            Reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to gain unauthorized access
            to the Services or related systems.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use the Services to build a competing product or service, or to
            benchmark without permission.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- User Content -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          5) User Content & License
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          You retain ownership of content you submit (“<strong
            >User Content</strong
          >”). You grant Protize a worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free
          license to host, store, reproduce, and display User Content as
          necessary to provide and improve the Services. You represent that you
          have all rights to grant this license and that your User Content
          complies with these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Intellectual Property -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          6) Intellectual Property
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          The Services, including text, graphics, logos, software, and other
          materials, are owned by Protize or our licensors and are protected by
          applicable intellectual property laws. Except as expressly permitted,
          you may not copy, modify, distribute, sell, or lease any part of the
          Services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Third-Party Services -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          7) Third-Party Services & Links
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          The Services may integrate with or link to third-party sites or
          services. We do not control and are not responsible for their content,
          policies, or practices. Your use of third-party services is at your
          own risk and may be subject to additional terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Fees -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          8) Fees, Payments & Taxes (If Applicable)
        </h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
          <li>
            Prices, features, and billing cycles may change with notice as
            required by law or contract.
          </li>
          <li>
            You authorize Protize and its payment processors to charge the
            provided payment method for subscriptions or purchases.
          </li>
          <li>
            You are responsible for any applicable taxes, duties, or government
            charges.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Privacy -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">9) Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Your use of the Services is also governed by our
          <a class="text-purple-700 underline" href="/privacy-policy"
            >Privacy Policy</a
          >, which explains how we collect and process personal data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Disclaimers -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">10) Disclaimers</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          THE SERVICES ARE PROVIDED “AS IS” AND “AS AVAILABLE.” TO THE MAXIMUM
          EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, PROTIZE DISCLAIMS ALL WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR
          IMPLIED, INCLUDING MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE,
          AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE SERVICES WILL BE
          UNINTERRUPTED, SECURE, OR ERROR-FREE.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Liability -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          11) Limitation of Liability
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, PROTIZE AND ITS AFFILIATES,
          OFFICERS, EMPLOYEES, AND AGENTS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT,
          INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS
          OF PROFITS, REVENUE, DATA, OR USE, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY.
          OUR TOTAL LIABILITY FOR ANY CLAIM RELATING TO THE SERVICES SHALL NOT
          EXCEED THE AMOUNT YOU PAID (IF ANY) FOR THE SERVICES DURING THE TWELVE
          (12) MONTHS PRECEDING THE EVENT GIVING RISE TO THE CLAIM.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Indemnity -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">12) Indemnification</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          You agree to indemnify and hold Protize and its affiliates, officers,
          employees, and agents harmless from any claims, liabilities, damages,
          losses, and expenses, including reasonable legal fees, arising out of
          or in any way connected with your use of the Services, your User
          Content, or your violation of these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Termination -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          13) Suspension & Termination
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          We may suspend or terminate your access to the Services, with or
          without notice, if we believe you have violated these Terms, pose a
          security risk, or for other lawful reasons. Upon termination, your
          right to use the Services ceases immediately. Sections intended to
          survive termination will continue to apply.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Governing Law -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          14) Governing Law & Dispute Resolution
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction where Protize
          is established, without regard to conflict-of-laws principles. Courts
          located in that jurisdiction shall have exclusive jurisdiction. Where
          required by law, you and Protize agree to attempt good-faith informal
          resolution before pursuing formal proceedings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Misc. -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">15) Miscellaneous</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
          <li>
            <strong>Entire Agreement:</strong> These Terms constitute the entire
            agreement between you and Protize regarding the Services.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Severability:</strong> If any provision is found unenforceable,
            the remaining provisions will remain in full force.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>No Waiver:</strong> Failure to enforce a provision is not a waiver
            of our right to do so later.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Assignment:</strong> You may not assign these Terms without our
            consent. We may assign them as part of a merger, acquisition, or sale
            of assets.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Force Majeure:</strong> We are not liable for delays or failures
            due to causes beyond our reasonable control.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Export Controls:</strong> You agree to comply with applicable
            export and sanctions laws.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">16) Contact Us</h2>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-4 text-gray-700">
          <p class="font-medium">Protize</p>
          <p>
            Email: <a
              href="mailto:support@protize.com"
              class="text-purple-700 underline">support@protize.com</a
            >
          </p>
          <!-- Optional:
          <p>Address: Your Business Address</p>
          -->
        </div>
      </section>

      <aside class="text-xs text-gray-500">
        <p>
          <strong>Note:</strong> These Terms are a general template tailored for
          a technology website and may require updates based on your products, fees,
          and jurisdiction. Please consult legal counsel to ensure compliance with
          applicable laws (e.g., consumer protection, e-commerce, and data protection
          rules).
        </p>
      </aside>
    </Container>
  </main>
</Layout>
